    4.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Seems decent, quality will only be known after time passes
    Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2024
    My kid graduated and moved out a few years ago so I'm in my house alone now. I generally keep the heat down in winter and just heat a room if I'm in it for any length of time. I have the gas fireplace for the great room / dining room / kitchen open area, as well... See more
    My kid graduated and moved out a few years ago so I'm in my house alone now. I generally keep the heat down in winter and just heat a room if I'm in it for any length of time. I have the gas fireplace for the great room / dining room / kitchen open area, as well as one of the Dyson air purifier / heater units. I had a smaller dyson heater for in the bedroom, but it wasn't as effective as I wanted for juts indirectly keeping it at a specific temp, so I thought I'd try this.

    Shipping was fine, no damage, and it's packed fairly well to help it travel in good condition. Assembly was just eight screws to attach the rolling feet, since this will be on the floor, not wall mounted, so I can move it around as desired.

    Took just a minute to get it up and running on my Echo, for smart voice control, and that works well.

    Unit is silent, other than on initial heating, a few creaks as parts expand. After the first minute, it's silent.

    Definitely does a good job of heating a small area. With my ceiling fan in my bedroom, this keeps it toasty and constant. I can even move it into the big open space great room area to assist with the other devices if I want.

    Love that my furnace doesn't have to do all the work heating laundry rooms, bathrooms, and three bedrooms when I'm not in it just to be a bit more comfy where I happen to be.

    I am a little disappointed with this heater but maybe my expectations were just too high. It does put out heat and if you are sitting next to it, or lying next to it like my dog prefers, you will stay nice and cozy. I was hoping it would heat my bedroom well, but all it really does is take the chill out. I have an old house and my bedroom stays very cold. We have an electric baseboard heater but it draws so much electricity so looked for an alternative. This is not quite what we were looking for. I can turn on my baseboard heater for about 20 or 30 minutes and it will heat the room much warmer than this heater will staying on constantly.
    It does have some good qualities though. It doesn't draw much electricity. We leave it on almost constantly and have not noticed on our electric bill. The buttons and screen are easy to operate. It's easy to move around, having a remote is handy and the wifi capability is great. I'm not saying this is not a good product; it just isn't what we were looking for for our purpose.

  • toddls
    5.0 out of 5 starsAmazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product
    WINNER. Best space heater Ever. Noiseless, instant heat, very sturdy construction (steel).
    Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2024
    So this is not another cheap plasticky fan based heater - but a steel encased convection heater. It arrives really well packaged, in inner and outer boxes, so shipping damage is unlikely. It's got a bit of 'mass' to it, so feels really sturdy,... See more
    So this is not another cheap plasticky fan based heater - but a steel encased convection heater.

    It arrives really well packaged, in inner and outer boxes, so shipping damage is unlikely.
    It's got a bit of 'mass' to it, so feels really sturdy, even on feet (supplied).

    The symbology on the display is a bit unfamiliar, but wasn't hard to mostly figure out with out the manual.

    The remote and SmartLife app are good, but probably a bit overkill, as you can pretty easily set this up manually for whatever (even just occasional) use case you have for it, from blasting heat in a cold room, or just watching for an 'open window' (a draft detecged by the temp sensor on teh bottom of the unit), or just need a bit of a heat boost from time to time.

    The thing is absolutely dead silent (well there was a very little crackling from expanding metals when I first turned it on) - the 'pilot' light is important, as it's the only way (other than heat) to know it's on!

    I set this up in a somewhat chilly office, and was really blown away by how quickly - and silently - it 'added heat' to the room - almost spooky how well it works!! Pretty much invisibly, too.

    (FYI, this room has baseboard electric heaters, AND in-joist copper hydronic heating in the ceilings.
    The former is noisy, slow and not very efficient; the hydronic system is by far the most efficient, but is slow to adapt to changes in temperatures (like an open window).
    I disabled the baseboard heaters at the breakers, but this new unit will be a nice little booster for times when there are drafts, or for sudden plunging temperatures.
    And is easy to move from room to room, as needed!)

    It comes with wall mount brackets attached to the back, or install feet for floor useage.

    Sure, electric space heaters are not the most energy efficient, compared to heat pumps, but this quality, performance, and durability (again - made of metal!) are superb, even for the price.

    If you have a cold room and need either a 'blaster' (1500 w) or just 'top up' (800 w setting),and want a really sturdy effective unit (it is NOT small - check out the dimensions to make sure you have room for it!).

    Compared to my old (ancient?) quartz tube heater, this is far more effective, absolutely silent (no fan noise to wake you as it cycles on and off), and much much 'smarter'!!

    Highly recommended!!
